\sum \limits_{n=1}^{\infty} n(2/3)^n
 \begin{align*} \sum_{n=1}^\infty n(2/3)^n &= \sum_{m=1}^\infty \sum_{n=m}^\infty (2/3)^n \\ &= \sum_{m=1}^\infty \frac{(2/3)^m}{1-2/3} \\ &= \frac{2/3}{(1-2/3)^2} = 6. \end{align*} 
f(x) := \sum \limits_{n=1}^{\infty} nx^n
